her than resolve their contradictions, their utterances held in tension “between the hemispheres of songbirds and the hemispheres of men.”  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aAmerican poetryy20th century. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  apoetry, poems, poet, contemporary, modern, mfa, award winning, william carlos williams prize, contradictions, contradictory, trauma, traumatic, gratitude, emotional, emotions, helplessness, dual citizenship, expression, politics, political, lyrical, essay, form, genre, race, class, classism, racism, culture, federal penitentiary, inmate, true story.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishz978311061036908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Studies 2019z9783110606348oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311068858040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226570556423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226570556/original  a978-3-11-061036-9  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural and Area Stud. 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-061076-5  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishb2019  a978-3-11-068858-0  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2019  aZDB-23-DKUb2019